==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: noninterchangeable
<hw>noninterchangeable</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(math,
logic)</fld> <def>not able to be interchanged without changing the truth
value.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not able to be substituted for each other; -- of
objects, such as parts of machinery; <as>as, the ink cartridges on the
new printer are <ex>noninterchangeable</ex> with those on the older
model.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>noninterference</ent>⟦br⟧
